{"word":"ἀναρ 2","slug":"ἀναρ 2","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n7343\" key=\"a)nar2\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"pref\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ἀναρ-</orth>: when <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀνά</foreign> is compd. with words beginning with <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ρ</itype>, the <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ρ</itype> is usually doubled, as in <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀναρραΐζω,</foreign> etc., though in Poets and <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion.\">Ion.</a></gram> </gramGrp> Greek it is sometimes single, as in sq.</entryFree>"}]}